          "text": "<p><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Dengue </span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 30-year-old individual is scheduled to donate blood for a local blood drive. To ensure the safety of the blood supply, the donor&#39;s blood will be screened for various infectious diseases. Among the following options, which one is typically NOT included in the routine screening for donated blood?</span></span></span></p>",
